James Brolin -LRB- -LSB- ˈbroʊlᵻn -RSB- born July 18 , 1940 -RRB- is an American actor , producer , and director , best known for his roles in film and television , including sitcoms and soap operas .
He is the father of actor Josh Brolin and husband of singer/actress Barbra Streisand .
Among other awards , Brolin has won two Golden Globes and an Emmy .
He received a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame on August 27 , 1998 .